Your **messageSender** should be an instance of **[HttpComponentsMessageSender][1]** instead of **[HttpUrlConnectionMessageSender][2]**. Also you need to provide proper credentials.

**[getConnection()][3]** function of **[TransportContext][4]** returns an implementation of **[WebServiceConnection][5]**. Both **[HttpUrlConnection][6]** and **[HttpComponentsConnection][7]** are implementations of the same. So basically you are getting the wrong type of connection,hence the *ClassCastException*.

The **ClientInterceptor** will work for custom headers but not for **Authorization** header. For that, your **HttpComponentsMessageSender** needs to be configured with your credentials.

